===Permanent charges===
After completion of [[The Fremennik Trials]], players can imbue their lyre into an [[enchanted lyre(i)]], which contains infinite charges, by offering Fossegrimen a one-off offering of 1,000 [[raw shark]]s, [[Raw bass|bass]], [[Raw manta ray|manta rays]] and [[Raw sea turtle|sea turtles]], costing {{Coins|{{GEP|Raw shark|1000}}+{{GEP|Raw bass|1000}}+{{GEP|Raw manta ray|1000}}+{{GEP|Raw sea turtle|1000}}}}. Fossegrimen will accept both noted and un-noted offerings, and they can be given in increments; she will inform players of the remaining amount required to imbue the lyre. When you charge the lyre to infinite, you must right click the altar choosing summon. Fossegrimen will explain the process and cost, until you are prompted to offer your noted fish, don't offer anything to the altar. 

The offering cost will drop by 200 raw fish ({{Coins|{{GEP|Raw shark|200}}+{{GEP|Raw bass|200}}+{{GEP|Raw manta ray|200}}+{{GEP|Raw sea turtle|200}}}}) for each tier of the [[Fremennik Diary]] completed. However, she will not return any fish once a higher tier of the diary has been completed.

